title: The Nanny
occurrences: Nanny, you're back. Mrs Fane doesn't want to go.
Nanny.
I'm frightened, Nanny. I'm frightened.
I know. But, Nanny, I don't want him home.
Oh, no. Nanny, I don't mean that.
I'm not going, Nanny.
Oh, no, Nanny. You tell him.
Nanny, you go with Mr Fane. Joey will like that.
Yes. Really, Nanny, I will be all right.
Something will have to be done about Mrs Fane, Nanny. This can't go on.
There's a nice surprise for you, Joey. You didn't expect Nanny to come and meet you.
- Then apologise to Nanny. - What for?
Doesn't he look marvellous, Nanny?
Nanny's worked so hard getting it ready for you. Wait till you see it.
But Joey, Nanny got it all ready especially for you.
You needn't do that. Nanny will do it for you.
Nanny was just going to unpack for you.
Of course he will, madam. He doesn't need his old nanny any more.
Nanny just wants you to be comfortable, darling.
- Nanny, I... - Madam, I must start to prepare dinner.
How was he with Nanny?
However much we may all depend upon Nanny,
Why do you like it more than the one Nanny arranged for you?
I know you do, but you see, Nanny is part of the family.
Don't forget that she was your mother's and Aunt Pen's nanny once upon a time.
We need Nanny to help us. Besides, I'm away a great deal of the time.
Look here, Joey. I'm aware that you don't get on with Nanny, but here she stays.
- Miss Penelope is here, sir. - Thank you, Nanny. I won't be a moment.
Oh, Nanny. Would you pack me a bag for tomorrow?
Good. Thank you, Nanny.
You've even got Nanny. I could certainly do with her, I can tell you.
Dear Nanny. One of the wonders of this age, you managing to hang on to her for so long.
Nanny gave up everything to stay and look after me.
- Her. - If you mean Nanny, say so. Is that who?
Now, that looks delicious, Nanny.
Nanny cooked it specially for your homecoming.
And that's not all. Show him, Nanny.
Nanny went out today to buy that, specially for you. Wasn't that kind of her?
- Nanny bought itjust for you. - I know.
Nanny understands. She's on your side.
- Nanny? - I don't want her to come in.
Nanny.
Yes, Nanny. Please will you brush my hair?
Nanny.
Of course it is. Haven't you got your old nanny here to make sure?
- Who's that? - Nanny.
Nanny?
- No. So Nanny told me. - What did she tell you?
Morning, Nanny.
Nanny.
I'm going to see if Nanny's all right. You keep out of trouble.
Nanny, why aren't you lying down?
Dear Nanny. You do try so hard.
What is it, Nanny?
All right, Nanny. I'll have another word with him.
- I only wish I could help. - You do help, Nanny.
- Where's yours, Nanny? - I'm not hungry, madam.
Nanny says you were sneaking in the kitchen.
- Well, I do. Apologise to Nanny. - No.
Come on, Nanny. Since when have you been unable to cope with a ten-year-old boy?
- We used to play for money at school. - So you told me. Yes, Nanny.
- I think it's humiliating, Nanny. Really, I do. - I don't mind.
Nanny.
Nanny.
Nanny...
Poor Nanny.
I'm going to tell Nanny you said that.
Are you hiding from Nanny?
It's a wonder I'm not stone dead. You realise that, don't you, Nanny?
- It's all right, Nanny, I can manage. - Well, I'd like to help you, Miss Pen.
Good night, Nanny.
Nanny?
For heaven's sake, don't wake him up, Nanny.
You get back to bed and Nanny will bring you a glass of warm milk.
And Nanny, don't take that pillow in.
What happened in the bathroom, Nanny?
You're not well. Let Nanny.
Master Joey wants to get rid of his old nanny. Did you know that?
Without Nanny, she'd be helpless.
And Nanny will have to go.
Are you hiding from Nanny?
Are you hiding from Nanny?
Thought your old nanny had forgotten you, didn't you?
Stop playing tricks on your old nanny.
I can't have Master Joey tell on his old nanny, can I?
You see, Miss Pen, being a nanny is based on trust.
You mustn't make it difficult for Nanny, Master Joey.
- I'm sorry about Nanny. - Don't think about it any more.
